added.title: Kabooms Part 1
added.description: The Titans are excited to see the movie version of their favorite show "Babies vs Dogs".

added.title: The Streak Part 1
added.description: It's Crime Season and Robin is determined to continue his streak of stopping 52 crimes every year.

added.title: The Streak Part 2
added.description: Robin's streak of stopping 52 crimes every year is in jeopardy when members of his team are poached by Kid Flash.

added.title: The Egg
added.description: To impress the mother of Anais' playdate, Nicole forces her family to get classy. Nicole arranges a playdate for Anais with the son of a classy lady she met at the supermarket. She hopes that socializing with the right sort of people will help her children climb Elmore's social ladder. The Wattersons try to impress, but ultimately cannot help revealing their true natures. The grown-ups become convinced they want nothing more to do with each other, just as Anais and her playdate discover how much they have in common.

added.title: The Roots
added.description: When Mom sees Darwin gazing longingly at a fish-tank, she thinks their mammalian lifestyle isn't fulfilling her adopted son and deep down he longs to connect with his fishy roots. So the family try to reconnect him with his aquatic culture. They try fish-food, fish-language and even fish clothes. But when none of it works, they realize they may have to let him go.

added.title: The Fuss
added.description: Nicole tries, and fails, to hide her disappointment when Richard and the kids fail to remember her special day. Richard has to figure out what special day he has actually forgotten and then make it a day to remember or else!

added.title: The Vase
added.description: Sick of Granny Jojo's ugly gifts, Nicole encourages the kids to take matters into their own hands and accidentally break her latest hideous vase. But when Gumball, Darwin and Anais try to destroy it, they discover it is more robust than it seems.

added.title: The List
added.description: When the kids find out that Mom's life hasn't panned out exactly as she'd hoped, they try to make her day a bit easier by taking on her chores. However, they accidentally grab her bucket list instead of her to-do list and end up attempting to tick off all of Nicole's life goals.

added.title: Apple's Focus
added.description: Apple helps Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

added.title: Folk Art Foes
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes the lord of mischief from an ancient relic, V and V have to work together to trap it back inside.

added.title: Suerte
added.description: When Vic cheats on an enchanted board game, the malevolent characters come to life, and it's up to V & V to figure out how to put them back in the game.

added.title: Brotherly Love
added.description: After breaking Chata's plant, Vic and Val must accomplish the seemingly easy task of replacing it; this proves difficult when their squabbling puts Monte Macabre in jeopardy.

added.title: Chata's Quinta Quinceañera
added.description: Vic and Val want to go to a friend's pool party on the same day as their grandma's quinceañera, so they use a magical flute that allows them to teleport and attend both at the same time.

added.title: Cleaning Day
added.description: Victor & Valentino gain a newfound respect for cleanliness after Chata's house traps them inside its labyrinth of ancient, magical walls.

added.title: The Babysitter
added.description: Vic & Val want to sneak out to a secret fireworks show but are thwarted when their new babysitter, Xochi, outsmarts them at every turn.

added.title: Hurricane Chata
added.description: When V & V discover that Chata's emotions control the water in the lake, they use it to their advantage and start their own wave pool business.

added.title: Dead Ringer
added.description: When Vic doesn't pick Val for his soccer team, Val vows to win with his own squad. But when his team doesn't match up, he resorts to supernatural means to win.

added.title: Legend of the Hidden Skate Park
added.description: While searching for a hidden skate park, V and V happen upon a tribe of wild kids, who live in a society without rules or adults.

added.title: Lonely Haunts Club
added.description: Instead of celebrating Valentine's Day, Vic & Val take on a dare to explore a haunted mansion with their rivals, Charlene & Pineapple.

added.title: Venthalla
added.description: Owen has his super ball confiscated and locked up in Chef's office. Duncan, seeing an opportunity to get help escaping the daycare, leads an away team into the vents to recover Owen's ball.

added.title: Duck Duck Juice
added.description: After daring each other to drink Chef's Pegasus Rainbow Latte, Izzy and Jude are jacked up like crazy and Duncan and Courtney take a road trip to try and replace the drink before Chef finds out it's gone.

added.title: Cluckwork Orange
added.description: After befriending a chicken with a bad attitude at a petting zoo, Jude is followed back to school by the chicken. He defends the bad bird's behavior until he can defend it no longer.

added.title: Free Chili
added.description: When Owen hides a walkie-talkie inside his chili dog, Harold believes it's an alien here to destroy Earth.

added.title: The Date
added.description: When Chef is happy he orders pizza for the kids, this gives Owen & Jude the idea to create a fake secret admirer for Chef.

added.title: Aquarium for a Dream
added.description: Gwen tries to convince Chef to tell the class the truth about their pet goldfish.

added.title: Cuttin' Corners
added.description: Duncan, Leshawna and Jude all want corner pieces of Izzy's Birthday Cake… But are they prepared to go to any length to get one?

added.title: Look Who's Clocking
added.description: When Harold's warnings not to mess with the clock go ignored, the kids are forced to save themselves when Duncan tears a hole in the fabric of time.

added.title: Harold Swatter and the Goblet of Flies
added.description: After finding what he believes to be a magic wand, Owen accidentally turns Harold into a housefly.

added.title: Stink. Stank. Stunk
added.description: When a skunk comes seeking its annual revenge on Chef, Duncan sees it as an opportunity to get a vacation from daycare.

added.title: Shhh!
added.description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

added.title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
added.description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

added.title: Animo Farm
added.description: Ben stumbles into Dr. Animo's secret lab now ruled by his superior mutants, the Alphas, and must help the lesser animals escape while stuck as Stinkfly.

added.title: Never Trust a Human
added.description: A flashback episode tells the story of Young Wu and Young Garmadon meeting Aspheera and teaching her the secrets of Spinjitzu.

added.title: Under Siege
added.description: Having learned Master Wu is the "Treacherous One," the ninja find themselves under siege at the Monastery, trying to protect Wu from the wrath of Aspheera.

added.title: Jessica Goes to the Creek
added.description: When Craig and Jessica are locked out of the house, Craig has no choice but to bring his little sister to the Creek.

added.title: The Final Book
added.description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

added.title: Too Many Treasures
added.description: Hoping to fix their fort, Craig enlists the 10 Speeds to give them a ride to the legendary Junk Pile.

added.title: Itch to Explore
added.description: Craig's quest to map the entire Creek takes him and his friends into the treacherous Poison Ivy Grove.

added.title: You're It
added.description: A vicious game of tag wreaks havoc on the Creek, claiming Kelsey as the next it.

added.title: Wildernessa
added.description: An encounter with Wildernessa, guardian of the wilderness, inspires Kelsey to take up a cause.

added.title: Artesanias traviesas
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic libera al señor de las travesuras del interior una reliquia antigua, V y V tienen que trabajar en equipo para volver a encerrarlo.

added.title: Futbol a Muerte
added.description: Cuando Vic no elige a Val para su equipo de fútbol, Val promete ganar con su propio equipo. Pero cuando su equipo no está a la altura, recurre a medios sobrenaturales para ganar.

added.title: Quintos Quinces
added.description: Victor y Valentino quieren ir a la fiesta en la piscina de un amigo el mismo día que la fiesta de quince años de su abuela, así que usan una flauta mágica que les permite teletransportarse y asistir a ambas al mismo tiempo.

added.title: La Leyenda del Parque Patinetas
added.description: Mientras buscan un parque de patinaje escondido, V y V se encuentran con una tribu de niños salvajes, que viven en una sociedad sin reglas ni adultos.

added.title: Amor de hermanos
added.description: Después de romper la planta de Chata, Vic y Val deben cumplir con la tarea aparentemente fácil de reemplazarla, lo cual demuestra no serlo cuando sus disputas ponen en peligro Monte Macabro.

added.title: Dia de limpieza
added.description: Victor y Valentino adquieren un nuevo respeto por la limpieza después de que la casa de Chata los atrapa dentro de su laberinto de paredes antiguas y mágicas.

added.title: La ninera
added.description: Vic y Val quieren colarse en un espectáculo secreto de fuegos artificiales, pero su plan se ve frustrado cuando su nueva niñera, Xochi, los supera en todo momento.

added.title: Huracan Chata
added.description: Cuando V y V descubren que las emociones de Chata controlan el agua del lago, deciden sacar ventaja y comienzan su propio negocio de piscinas de olas.

added.title: Loteria
added.description: Cuando Vic hace trampa en un juego de mesa encantado, los malvados personajes cobran vida, y V y V son los responsables de averiguar cómo volver a ponerlos en el juego.

added.title: El club de los solitarios
added.description: En lugar de celebrar el Día de San Valentín, Vic y Val se atreven a explorar una mansión encantada con sus rivales, Charlene y Piña.

added.title: My Dad Can Beat up Your Dad
added.description: When a bully says his dad can beat up KO's mom, KO gladly accepts the challenge on Carol's behalf.

added.title: Know Your Mom
added.description: KO wants to surprise Carol with a gift for Mother's Day, but doesn't know what to get her.

added.title: Glory Days
added.description: KO does a school report on Carol.

added.title: Let's Take a Moment
added.description: Mr. Gar and Carol fight a villain from their past.

added.title: My Fair Carol
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up to help Carol out with a special occasion.

added.title: The First Day
added.description: Best friends Oscar and Hedgehog get dropped off at their first day at summer camp.

added.title: Monster Babies
added.description: Alice lures Oscar and his monster friends for a tea party, but only to turn the monsters into cute babies.

added.title: Chocolate Money Badgers
added.description: Oscar learns that he can earn merit badges that unlock prizes.

added.title: Saxophone Come Home
added.description: Oscar befriends a teenage Yeti.

added.title: Pajama Pajimjams
added.description: Oscar pretends to be a talking pair of pajamas named "Jimjams" to make his friend Pajamas happy.

added.title: Oscar & Hedgehog's Melody
added.description: Susie holds the annual talent show that has the rest of the campers competing to win.

added.title: Feeling Spacey
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog arrive on a planet that has no emotions.

added.title: Ghost the Boy
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog befriend a ghost who can't remember who he is.

added.title: Computer Vampire
added.description: Oscar finds a mysterious old video game in the library.

added.title: The Basketball Liaries
added.description: With the help from Basketball, Oscar makes an impressive shot that scores him a spot on the Gold League.

added.title: Chili Cook-Off
added.description: Benson wants to get some street cred with the Park Managers' Association and win the big chili cook-off.

added.title: Guys Night 2
added.description: The guys want to give Thomas an epic Guys Night before he goes into hiding forever.

added.title: Eileen Flat Screen
added.description: Rigby wants to set up Eileen's flat screen TV for her.

added.title: Sad Sax
added.description: Mordecai wants to get back together with C.J.

added.title: I See Turtles
added.description: Eileen and the gang want to see baby sea turtles hatch and go into the ocean.

added.title: Joshua & Margaret Investigations
added.description: Finn and Jake's parents hunt an unearthly menace in the woods.

added.title: Kabums Part 1
added.description: Los Titanes están ansiosos por ver la versión cinematográfica de su programa favorito, "Bebés vs. perros", hasta que la presentación de la película hace que se vuelva superaburrida de ver. Para salvarla, los Titanes se meten en la película e interrumpen la charla con mucha acción fascinante.

added.title: Jake the Dad
added.description: Jake's a daddy, but being a father and keeping his rainicorn pups from killing themselves or each other is a lot harder than he imagined.

added.title: La Racha Parte 1
added.description: Llega la temporada de delitos, y Robin está decidido a continuar su racha de impedir 52 delitos por año.

added.title: La Racha Parte 2
added.description: La racha de Robin de impedir 52 delitos por año se pone en peligro cuando los miembros de su equipo se convierten en presas de Kid Flash.

added.title: Gone to His Head
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's new found confidence makes his head big.

added.title: You Can't Handle the Tooth
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus must rescue Pizza Steve from the Tooth Fairy.

added.title: Robo-UG
added.description: Uncle Grandpa builds a robot version of himself to help with his duties.

added.title: Memory of a Memory
added.description: To save Marceline from a sleep spell, Finn and Jake must enter her mind and find the wake spell deep inside her memory.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Pizza Eve
added.description: Uncle Grandpa falls for Pizza Steve's "girlfriend" and ends up in serious danger.

added.title: The Return of Aunt Grandma
added.description: Aunt Grandma is back and still bent on ruining Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Rock Show
added.description: Chad's band Dogmon, plays a show for the first time in years, giving Clarence and Mary a chance to really rock out.

added.title: Jake vs. Me-Mow
added.description: Finn and Jake grapple with a tiny feline assassin.

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: Alien Hunt! With Meteorfire and Cosmos Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee enlists washed-up TV show host Meteorfire to help him find another of Windblade's psychic shards on Luna-3.

added.title: Alien Hunt! With Meteorfire and Cosmos Part 2
added.description: Bumblebee runs the gauntlet of creepily haunted Luna-3, while Meteorfire records everything on camera for his show.

added.title: Journey to the Valley of Repugnus Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee and Grimlock are separated as they search the depths of Cybertron for another of Windblade's psychic shards, encountering the Monsterbots and the Energon Masters.

added.title: Journey to the Valley of Repugnus Part 2
added.description: Bee and Grimlock navigate the strange cultures of the Energon Masters and Monsterbots, uncovering a shocking secret about the two seemingly-different peoples.

added.title: Wild Wild Wheel Part 2
added.description: WildWheel finds Optimus Prime rebuilding a small Cybertronian town, only to discover the Prime does not recognize him.

added.title: Thunderhowl Part 2
added.description: Released after eons of imprisonment, Thunderhowl helps Bee and Chromia navigate the dangerous Crystal City.

added.title: Thunderhowl Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee and Chromia travel to Crystal City to recover one of Windblade's psychic shards and encounter a long-lost bot.

added.title: Wild Wild Wheel Part 1
added.description: A dangerous lone gunslinger named WildWheel returns to Cybertron looking for Optimus Prime.

added.title: Midnight at the Mayor's Mansion
added.description: When the Mayor's mansion is stalked by a vicious, ghostly monster, he calls the Powerpuff Girls for help.

added.title: The Trouble With Bubbles
added.description: When Bubbles is overworked, she uses her coding skills to come up with a new solution.

added.title: Ghost Town Part 1
added.description: When Windblade mysteriously steals the Allspark, Optimus, Bumblebee, Hot Rod and Cheetor follow her to a strange abandoned city.

added.title: Ghost Town Part 2
added.description: Teletraan-X attempts to rehabilitate Starscream while Optimus, Bee, Hot Rod and Cheetor's quest to save Windblade uncovers a city that is more than meets the eye.

added.title: Perfect Storm Part 1
added.description: Arcee and Grimlock go off on an adventure only to return and discover the Ark without power and their friends all in stand-by mode.

added.title: Perfect Storm Part 2
added.description: Arcee and Grimlock get an adventure they never bargained for as they protect the helpless Ark from all manner of space anomalies.

added.title: The Crossroads Part 1
added.description: An attempt to use a derelict SpaceBridge sends The Ark to Unspace!

added.title: The Crossroads Part 2
added.description: Optimus and the Autobots team up with some very familiar faces to escape Unspace.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: El pollo maniaco
added.description: Después de hacerse amigo de un pollo con mala actitud en un zoológico de contacto, este lo sigue de regreso a la escuela. Él defiende la mala conducta del ave hasta que ya no puede seguir haciéndolo.

added.title: El Libro Final
added.description: El último libro de fantasía de la serie favorita de Kelsey desaparece de la biblioteca. Por eso, Craig decide ayudarla a resolver el misterio de quién se lo llevó.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Chile libre
added.description: Cuando Owen oculta un walkie talky dentro de su perro con chile, Harold cree que es un alienígena que vino a destruir la tierra.

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: Demasiados Tesoros
added.description: Con la esperanza de reparar su fuerte, Craig consigue la ayuda de Los Veloces Diez para llevarlos hasta la legendaria pila de basura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La cita
added.description: Cuando Chef está feliz ordena pizza para los niños. Esto le da a Owen & Jude la idea de crear una falsa admiradora secreta para Chef.

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: La pecera de los suenos
added.description: Gwen trata de convencer a Chef de que le diga a la clase la verdad sobre su pececito dorado.

added.title: La Melancolia de Oscar y Erizo
added.description: Susie organiza el concurso anual de talentos, y todos los campistas compiten para ganar.

added.title: Salvajessa
added.description: Un encuentro con Salvajessa, guardiana de la naturaleza, inspira a Kelsey a dedicarse a una causa.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Man Up
added.description: When Buttercup's aggression inadvertently allows villain Man-Boy to escape, she starts a new-age lifestyle in an effort to be more calm. But when Man-Boy returns to enact his revenge, Buttercup must embrace the balance between punching and hugging in order to defeat him.

added.title: Conquistando torres
added.description: Duncan, Leshawna y Jude quieren una pieza de esquina del pastel de cumpleaños de Izzy, pero, ¿están preparados para hacer cualquier cosa por conseguir uno?

added.title: Sintiendose Especiales
added.description: Oscar y Erizo llegan a una planeta que no tiene emociones.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: Fantasma, El Nino
added.description: Oscar y Erizo se hacen amigos de un fantasma que no recuerda quién es.

added.title: Little Octi Lost
added.description: Buttercup steals Octi to teach Bubbles a lesson but ends up wanting to keep him for herself.

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Vampiro de Computadora
added.description: Oscar encuentra un videojuego viejo y misterioso en la biblioteca.

added.title: Cronicas de Mentiras Basquetboleras
added.description: Con la ayuda de Basketball, Oscar hace un tiro impresionante que le permite conseguir un lugar en la Liga Dorada.

added.title: Power Up Puff
added.description: During a fight, both Buttercup and Bubbles are surprised to discover they've leveled up, leaving Blossom to wonder when or if she'll get new powers too.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
added.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

added.title: A Small Problem
added.description: When Ben is not allowed on an attraction at a water park because he to short, he decides to go alien to get even with the ride's attendant.

added.title: Drill of the Hunt
added.description: Mega Man tries a quick fix using Hypno Woman's powers to rehabilitate Drill Man, to disastrous results!

added.title: Malefactor
added.description: Khyber and his dog attacks Ben and Rook while they're at the "Olde Bellwood Days" festival, but does the hunter have other plans? (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Hypnotick.)

added.title: Que ocurre con Dan
added.description: Cuando Dan se comporta de forma extraña con los Fantásticos, Lightning olfatea la verdad: iUn impostor!

added.title: Matter of the Mind/Core Cell
added.description: Matter of Mind: Drago leads the Bakugan against the threat of Tiko to protect a powerful energy source called the Core Cell./Core Cell: The AO defend the Core Cell from an attack by Tiko and in a last ditch effort to save it Dan manages to evolve Drago into his L2 form.

added.title: Power Cycle
added.description: After replicating Elec Man's powers, an underslept/overcharged Mega Man goes on a 24/7 hero spree that ends up turning him into his own worst enemy.

added.title: Una necesidad inquietante
added.description: La aparición de un nuevo campo Bakugan hace que los chicos del pueblo corran a buscar a sus propios Bakugan. Pero cuando el campo es contaminado, Lia debe salvarlos a todos.

added.title: Subterranean Homesick Blues/Honey Struck
added.description: Subterranean Homesick Blues: The AO return home to learn that no time has passed but they soon discover their knowledge of brawling has gotten years more advanced./Honey Struck: After Strata is sent packing the AO discover that they have picked up a hitchhiker a Panda-like Bakugan who is nothing but sticky trouble.

added.title: Bored to Be Wild
added.description: Mega Man teams up with his crush, Ashley Adderley, to solve a series of science riddles left by Chemical Man, who's plotting to turn all the city's metal into rubber.

added.title: Tutores Bakugan
added.description: Dan y Wynton conocen a un extraño chico que los lleva a un laberinto subterráneo, donde descubren que el Bakugan del chico ha sido esclavizado.

added.title: Shun Shine/Ronin Son
added.description: Shun Shine: The AO want to evolve their Bakugan like Dan did with Drago but only Shun finds a way by tapping into the energy of the Mind Core Cell./Ronin Son: When Shun's cousin Masato Kazami claims Hydorous as his intellectual property the AO must battle to keep their friend by their side.

added.title: Enter the Wood Man
added.description: Mega Man accidentally awakens Wood Man, who thinks it's still the Hard Age, sets off on a path of destruction toward Silicon City.

added.title: Lightfall Part 1
added.description: The mysterious Lord Obsidian calls Mega Man a traitor to robots and challenges him to a duel. An overconfident Mega Man is humbled by this mysterious new villain.

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself. (Guest-starring Aziz Ansari as Ben 23.)

added.title: Hurricane Dilliss
added.description: Things in the Wendle household are turned upside down when Mary's mom Dyllis comes to visit, butting her way into every corner of Clarence, Mary and Chad's life.

added.title: Magnus P.I.
added.description: There's a been a string of thefts and each one has involved a Bakugan. The AAAnimus security force have decided the only brawler who could be responsible is: Magnus. The shock of this accusation sets Magnus off to takes justice in his own hands and go after the thief himself./Magnus foils the latest burglary attempt by the phantom thief, and in doing so, discovers the brawler partners with a golden Bakugan.  Magnus is now more interested in a brawl, than stopping any crime.

added.title: Awesome Brawlers Training  Camp
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers head to a training facility owned by Kasami International to prepare for the Bakugan Battle League - Los Volmos. But once the gang figures out they will all be competing against each other for the same title, the "team building" retreat doesn't quite go as planned./Agit turns up at the Kasami training facility and fits right in with the Awesome brawlers. This is a lifestyle that he can get used to, but it becomes apparent Agit is torn between a life as a phantom thief and life as a brawler.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League Begins/Riot vs. Ajit
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League Begins: The qualifying rounds for the Bakugan Battle league are taking place all around Los Volmos. The Awesome Brawlers all make it through into the tournament without a hitch, that is all but Dan. Dan faces an old rival in Trey, who's back with a few tricks up his sleeve./Riot vs. Ajit: The Bakugan battle league is finally here and 16 brawlers have qualified to enter including all the Awesome Brawlers. The first round will feature a brawl between China Riot and the golden Bakugan brawler, Agit!

added.title: Kung Fu Master/A Battle of Popularity
added.description: Kung Fu Master: Dan's first match-up of the Bakugan battle league is the Chinese Champion Brawler: Zhao. His opponent is a deeply focused, and serious brawler, who uses Kung Fu techniques in battle. It's going to take all Dan and Drago's focus and strength to get through this opponent!/A Battle of Popularity: Shun and Wynton's first match-ups in the Bakugan battle league take place at the same time. Even though they're not battling each other, Wynton can't help getting a little competitive with Shun, bragging that he can get the crowd cheering louder than Shun. The brawls quickly turn into a popularity contest, instead of a Bakugan battle!

added.title: The Mysterious Revenger/Wynton vs. Lia
added.description: The Mysterious Revenger: It's the quarter finals of the Bakugan Battle League, the top eight brawlers are set to face off! In this round, Dan will face off against the Bakugan rocker - Revenger! These two brawlers give it their all in this icy cold clash!/Wynton Vs. Lia: The quarter finals continue, and it's the first Awesome Brawler vs. Awesome Brawler matches of the Bakugan Battle League tournament. In this round, it's Wynton vs. Lia and Shun vs. Lightning.

added.title: Dawn Before Dusk
added.description: Dawn Before Dusk, Part 1: The AO meet Benton Dusk discovering that their quiet little corner of the world is about to become much, much larger./Dawn Before Dusk, Part 2: Benton Dusk reveals that the AO have been indentified as persons of interest by powerful corporations including Philomena Dusk's AAAnimus.

added.title: Stratified/Maze Daze
added.description: Stratified: The AO embark on a mission into the mysterious labyrinth world of Vestroia to find Strata the Hunter and free the Bakugan he has imprisoned./Maze Daze: Lost in the maze of Vestroia the AO encounter powerful forces that seem to be struggling for control over the alien landscape.

added.title: All Jungled Up/Outer Demons
added.description: All Jungled Up: Still lost in Vestroia the AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko./Outer Demons: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining created by the Core Cell.

added.title: Running Wild
added.description: Student elections get blown out of proportion (literally) when Air Man lends his support to Aki's rival for class president, Peter Punk.

added.title: Unfriendly Competition
added.description: Aki must set aside a petty rivalry with Bert Wily in order to stop Chemistry Man from wreaking havoc at Silicon Central's Field Day.

added.title: Opposites Attract
added.description: Fire Man and Wave Man team up to evaporate the city's water supply, forcing Mega Man to team up with an ally of his own- Suna.

added.title: I.C.E. (In Case of Emergency)
added.description: When Ice Man decides to be a hero, Mega Man, influenced by Ice Man's literalness, steps down from the hero biz until a true crisis snaps him out of it.

added.title: Trust Your Guts, Man!
added.description: Guts Man tries to undo Dr. Light's eco-friendly disposal of trash in Silicon City by infiltrating the family and destroying the Lighthouse so he can eat it!

added.title: Clarence's Stormy Sleepover - Episode 1: The Phantom Clarence
added.description: Clarence is determined to throw the sleepover to end all sleepovers, his biggest party yet! Decorations, pillow fights, games. He's got it all. There's only one thing missing, guests! Clarence sets out to invite all his friends in town, but finds that they might need some convincing.

added.title: Clarence's Stormy Sleepover - Episode 3: Badgers N' Bunkers
added.description: As Sumo's dad Mel prepares the family for over-the-top doomsday scenarios, Sumo struggles to convince his family to let him keep a new pet.

added.title: Clarence's Stormy Sleepover - Episode 5: Bye Bye Baker
added.description: An ever-cheerful Clarence attempts to improvise a sleepover party with some of Aberdale's townsfolk in an unusual location - while everyone else panics.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: While watching a TV show about dreams, Clarence dozes off and enters the whimsical dreamscape that hovers above Aberdale. Here Clarence can see other people's dreams, experiencing the subconscious of all his friends and neighbors. But when things turn nightmarish, Clarence must find a way to escape back to reality.

added.title: Spooky Boo
added.description: After Clarence leads a few neighborhood kids through his homemade haunted house, Chelsea suggests they go to the high school kids haunted house for some real scares. When the gang makes a wrong turn they find themselves in a mysterious house on a hill full of creepy sounds, ghoulish shadows and mutant rat men!

added.title: Escape From Earth Part 1
added.description: Optimus struggles to recover from using the Matrix of Leadership while the Autobots attempt to get the Allspark back to Cybertron.

added.title: Escape From Earth Part 2
added.description: With the Ark extricated from Mt. St. Hilary, the Autobots must run the gauntlet of Decepticon forces to escape Earth with the Allspark.

added.title: Party Down Part 1
added.description: On their way to back to Cybertron, the Autobots attempt to have some well-deserved fun by throwing a party.

added.title: Party Down Part 2
added.description: A malfunction in Wheeljack's party favors turns most of the Autobot crew feral, leaving Optimus, Cheetor, and Teletraan-X in a race to save their friends.

added.title: Wiped Out Part 1
added.description: Out in space to catch some solar waves, Bumblebee, Hot Rod and Cheetor discover the asteroid remains of a mysterious planet.

added.title: Wiped Out Part 2
added.description: Separated from his friends, Cheetor is captured by the territorial Sharkticons who enlist him in their fight over the last remaining bits of their destroyed planet.

added.title: Ventila-hala
added.description: Chef le confisca la mega-bola a Owen y la guarda en su oficina. Duncan, viendo una oportunidad para conseguir ayuda escapando de la guardaería, lidera un equipo de fuga por los conductos del aire acondicionado para recuperarla.

added.title: Ganas de Explorar
added.description: La misión de Craig de mapear el Arroyo entero los lleva a él y a sus amigos a arboleda traicionera de Hiedra Venenosa
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Primer Dia
added.description: Las familias de Oscar y Erizo, que son mejores amigos, los dejan en su primer día de campamento de verano.

added.title: Monstruos Bebes
added.description: Alice tienta a Oscar y a sus amigos monstruos para que asistan a un té festivo, pero el objetivo real es convertir a los monstruos en tiernos bebés.

added.title: Jugo arcoiris
added.description: Después de desafiarse unos a otros a tomar el Latte de Pegaso de Chef, Izzy y Jude están llenos de energía y Duncan y Courtney hacen un viaje por carretera para tratar de reemplazar la bebida antes de que Chef descubra que desapareció.

added.title: La Traes
added.description: Un despiadado juego de persecución desata un caos en el Arroyo, y se declara a Kelsey como la próxima perseguidora.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Insignias de Choco Monedas
added.description: Oscar se entera de que puede ganar medallas al mérito que desbloquean premios.

added.title: Jessica va al Arroyo
added.description: Cuando Craig y Jessica quedan encerrados fuera de la casa, Craig no tiene otra opción: debe llevar a su hermanita al Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Saxofon vuelve a casa
added.description: Oscar se hace amigo de un Yeti adolescente.

added.title: Pijamas Pijamas
added.description: Oscar finge hablar con unos pijamas llamados "Jimjams" para hacer feliz a su amigo Pijama.

added.title: Shhh
added.description: Mientras Ben se relaja en un monasterio con una política de silencio, no puede quedarse callado y, por accidente, despierta a un peligroso Dragón oculto en una recámara secreta bajo los salones sagrados...una tarea que podría ser demasiado para manejar, iincluso para Diamante!

added.title: La Breve Carrera De La Nina Suertuda
added.description: Cuando un hechicero jugador de cosplay pone las manos sobre una varita mágica real en la convención Comic Con, Ben consigue la ayuda de Gwen para impedir que Hex la recupere: Gwen engaña al hechicero malvado y le hace creer que es una poderosa maga...ila única e inimitable Niña Suertuda!

added.title: Rebelion En La Granja
added.description: Ben encuentra el laboratorio secreto del Doctor Ánimo -ahora gobernado por los alfas, sus mutantes superiores- y debe ayudar a los animales inferiores mientras está atrapado en forma de Insectoide.

added.title: Jamas Confies en un Humano
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: Sitiados
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que el Maestro Wu es el "Traicionero", los ninja se encuentran asediados en el Monasterio, tratando de proteger a Wu de la ira de Aspheera.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos conocen a Benton Dusk y descubren que su pequeño mundo está a punto de volverse mucho más grande.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 2
added.description: Benton Dusk revela que Los Fantásticos son considerados personas de interés por poderosas corporaciones como AAAnimus.

added.title: Stratificados
added.description: Los Fantásticos emprenden una misión en el misterioso mundo laberíntico de Vestroia para buscar a Strata El Cazador y liberar a los Bakugan que tiene presos.

added.title: Manzana, Concentrate
added.description: Manzana ayuda a Cebollín a cumplir su sueño de competir en un programa de pastelería.

removed.title: Fideito
removed.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben seguir teniendo la onda suficiente para aparecer en el video musical de su rapero favorito.

removed.title: Lil Noodle
removed.description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.
